title: -Polarization Measurements and Optical Model Analyses of Neutron Scattering At 3.2 Mev -

x4codes.shortRef: Jour: Nuclear Physics, Section A, Vol.222, Issue.1, p.93 (1974)

x4freetext: FURNISHED A 650 KEV DEUTERON BEAM WITH A MEAN
.THE NEUTRON PRODUCING TARGETS WERE 1 MG/CM2 TITANIUM
DEUTERIUM TARGETS WITH COPPER BACKING PLACED AT 45
.MEAN NEUTRON ENERGY WAS 3.2 MEV AND TOTAL WIDTH OF
.NEUTRONS WERE COLLIMATED TO A NARROW BEAM THE WIDTH
OF WHICH WAS THE SAME AS THE SCATTERER DIAMETER.
.THEIR LENGTHS AND DIAM VARIED BETWEEN RESPECTIVELY
24 AND 40 MM AND 30 AND 50 MM BUT WERE ALWAYS SMALLER
THAN THE MEAN FREE PATH FOR 3.2 MEV NEUTRONS.
.MEASUREMENTS MADE BY TRANSMISSION AND RESTRICTED TO
5 CM IN DIAM,7.5 CM IN LENGTH COULD BE POSITIONED AT
ANGLES BETWEEN 30 AND 150 DEGREES IN A LARGE PARAFFIN
WITH P1= -15 PERCENT,BY THE FOLLOWING FORMULA.
WHERE- P(COR) IS THE CORRECTED DATUM
- F THE CORRECTION FACTOR FOR INELASTIC SCAT.
- A,B,C TERMS WHICH DEPEND OF THE FOLDED
.COMPARISON WITH OTHER DATA AND OPTICAL MODEL ANALYSES.
